From: Kamil Bienkiewicz <perceivalpercy@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 22 May 2026 13:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] net: ethernet: qcom: ppe: edma: store full 64-bit opaque skb
 pointer in descriptors

EDMA_RXFILL_OPAQUE_HI_SET / EDMA_TXDESC_OPAQUE_HI_SET (and their
respective call sites) are gated on `#ifdef __LP64__`. That's a
userspace toolchain macro defined by glibc/musl — it is **NOT**
defined when the kernel is compiled. The kernel uses CONFIG_64BIT
instead.

On a 64-bit aarch64 kernel, the result is that only the low 32 bits
of the opaque skb pointer are written to the descriptor's word2.
word3 (the high half) stays zero. When edma_rx_napi_poll later
reconstructs `skb = (uintptr_t)(word2 | (word3 << 32))` it gets
something like 0x0000000000847000 — a userspace-looking value —
instead of the true ffffffc0... kernel pointer.

The reap loop then dereferences this NULL-high-half "skb" pointer
in `skb->dev = ndev` and oopses with "Unable to handle kernel
write to read-only memory at virtual address 0x..." where the
address is a small offset into a value that should have been an
sk_buff base.

This was the actual root cause behind the two earlier oopses at
edma_rx_napi_poll+0x134 (skb=0x1e) and +0x168 (skb=0x10) — both
the same "low-32-bits-of-an-skb pointer" pattern.

Fix all three occurrences (rx caller, rx header macro definition,
tx header macro definition) to use CONFIG_64BIT instead of
__LP64__.

Signed-off-by: Kamil Bienkiewicz <perceivalpercy@gmail.com>
---
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/qualcomm/ppe/edma_rx.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/qualcomm/ppe/edma_rx.c
@@ -92,7 +92,7 @@ static int edma_rx_alloc_buffer_list(str
 		EDMA_RXFILL_BUFFER_ADDR_SET(rxfill_desc, buff_addr);
 
 		EDMA_RXFILL_OPAQUE_LO_SET(rxfill_desc, skb);
-#ifdef __LP64__
+#ifdef CONFIG_64BIT
 		EDMA_RXFILL_OPAQUE_HI_SET(rxfill_desc, skb);
 #endif
 		EDMA_RXFILL_PACKET_LEN_SET(rxfill_desc,
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/qualcomm/ppe/edma_rx.h
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/qualcomm/ppe/edma_rx.h
@@ -108,7 +108,7 @@
 
 #define EDMA_RXFILL_OPAQUE_LO_SET(desc, ptr)	(((desc)->word2) = \
 						(u32)(uintptr_t)(ptr))
-#ifdef __LP64__
+#ifdef CONFIG_64BIT
 #define EDMA_RXFILL_OPAQUE_HI_SET(desc, ptr)	(((desc)->word3) = \
 						(u32)((u64)(ptr) >> 0x20))
 #endif
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/qualcomm/ppe/edma_tx.h
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/qualcomm/ppe/edma_tx.h
@@ -76,7 +76,7 @@
 				(FIELD_PREP(EDMA_TXDESC_SERVICE_CODE_MASK, x)))
 #define EDMA_TXDESC_BUFFER_ADDR_SET(desc, addr)	(((desc)->word0) = (addr))
 
-#ifdef __LP64__
+#ifdef CONFIG_64BIT
 #define EDMA_TXDESC_OPAQUE_GET(_desc) ({ \
 			typeof(_desc) (desc) = (_desc); \
 			(((u64)(desc)->word3 << 32) | (desc)->word2); })
